Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da "cin zarafi" ta hanyar "tallace-tallacen farfaganda"
Mako guda bayan da jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani shafi hudu a jaridar Amurka da ke tallata cinikayyar Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka don yada farfaganda.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump a ranar Laraba ya yi magana game da wani karin bayani da aka biya na jaridar China Daily a cikin jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a Iowa, Des Moines Register, bayan da ya zargi China da son tsoma baki a zaben majalisar dokokin Amurka na ranar 6 ga Nuwamba, wanda China ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi na cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka bayyana a wata sanarwa da suka yi wa Reuters a matsayin wani sabon mataki na yakin neman zabe na Washington don matsa lamba kan kasar Sin.
Duk da cewa al'ada ce ga gwamnatocin kasashen waje su sanya tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna cikin yakin cinikayya wanda ya haifar da hauhawar harajin shigo da kayayyaki.
Sakamakon da China ta yi a farkon yakin cinikayya an tsara shi ne don cutar da masu fitar da kayayyaki a jihohi kamar Iowa waɗanda ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, in ji masana na kasar Sin da Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa China, ya ce Beijing ta cutar da ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni.
A wata kasida a jaridar Des Moines Register, Branstad ya ce China "yana kara yawan wannan cin zarafin ta hanyar tallata tallace-tallace a cikin jaridarmu ta kyauta".
"Ta hanyar yada farfagandar ta, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi amfani da al'adun Amurka na 'yancin magana da' yancin manema labarai ta hanyar sanya tallace-tallace a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
Ya rubuta cewa, "A akasin haka, a kan kiosks na jaridu a titunan Beijing za ku ga muryoyin adawa da iyaka kuma ba za ku ga ainihin ra'ayoyin da jama'ar kasar Sin za su iya yi game da matsalar tattalin arzikin kasar Sin ba saboda kafofin yada labarai suna karkashin matsin lamba daga jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin".
Ya kara da cewa wasu daga cikin manyan jaridun kasar Sin sun ki buga labarinsa, ko da yake bai bayyana jaridar da ya rubuta ba.
